<P>
   MENTAL-HEALTH _ One in every five Americans experiences a mental
disorder in any given year, and half of all Americans have such
disorders at some time in their lives, but most of them never seek
treatment, the surgeon general of the United States says in a
comprehensive new report. By Robert Pear.
</P>
<P>
   TRIPP-LEWINSKY _ For the first time since their fateful
friendship and taped conversations set off the investigation of
President Clinton, Monica Lewinsky and Linda Tripp will confront
each other again, this time in court. Ms. Lewinsky is on the
witness list for a pretrial hearing that is scheduled to begin on
Monday in Howard County, Maryland, where Ms. Tripp faces charges
that she illegally taped their telephone calls.
