<P>
   GM-NORTHAMERICA (Detroit) _ Despite slowing sales and bulging
inventories of unsold automobiles, the General Motors Corp.
announced on Friday that it planned to continue running its North
American factories at close to full speed through the first quarter
of next year. By Keith Bradsher.
</P>
<P>
   WTO-FUTURE (Geneva) _ Struggling to recover from a
violence-scarred conference in Seattle that collapsed in failure a
week ago, the World Trade Organization plans a special meeting on
Dec. 17 to decide how to proceed. By Robert Olsen.
</P>
<P>
   NORWEGIAN-CRUISE (Undated) _ Officials of Norwegian Cruise Line,
who have rejected a $1.7 billion takeover bid by the Carnival
Corporation, disclosed a rosy financial outlook on Friday in what
analysts said was an appeal to shareholders tempted by the offer.
By Edwin McDowell.
</P>
<P>
   UPN-MOESHA (Undated) _ UPN wants ``Moesha,'' the biggest comedy
hit in the brief history of the network, to go off into what one
network executive called ``new creative directions'' _ and the
show's new executive producers are willing to do it. By Bill
Carter.
</P>
<P>
