<P>
   WOMENS-FOOTBALL (Uniondale, N.Y.) _ The ladies couldn't throw,
at least not as much as they wanted to, in 40 mph gusts. The wind
kept them from kicking, too. So the New York Sharks, full of
adrenaline and athleticism, used a mean running game to defeat the
Minnesota Vixens, 12-6. It was a momentous day, especially for the
Sharks, a squad that put on the pads only about three weeks ago.
The Vixens, members of the Women's Professional Football League,
have four games under their belts, and have been on the field since
the beginning of October on a barnstorming tour to gauge the
interest in and audience for what the league advertises as ``high
quality smash mouth tackle football.'' By Tina Kelley.
</P>
