<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-WARREN-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WARREN SHUCKS BURDEN TO CARRY TEAM
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CHAREAN WILLIAMS 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ The last time we left running back Chris Warren,
Dallas Cowboys fans were ready to run him out of town. After
Sunday, he might have the run of it.
</P>
<P>
   After starter Emmitt Smith was injured on the first series,
Warren came in to gain 138 total yards in leading the Cowboys to a
20-10 victory against the Philadelphia Eagles.
</P>
<P>
   ``For Chris to come out and play the way he did, that was an
impressive showing by him,'' Cowboys coach Chan Gailey said.
``That's why he's on the team, to give us that ability to go out
there and run like that.''
</P>
<P>
   Warren lost two fumbles and his job in the 27-13 victory against
the Green Bay Packers on Nov. 14. In the next three games, he had
three carries for 7 yards. Against the Eagles, he carried the
Cowboys.
</P>
<P>
   Warren ran 25 times for 92 yards and a touchdown as the Cowboys
gained 112 rushing yards. He also had four catches for 46 yards.
</P>
<P>
   ``I never thought about that \RGreen Bay game\S,'' Warren said.
``I just wanted to go out and play well today. I didn't think about
last week or next week.''
</P>
<P>
   On the first play from scrimmage, Smith gained 2 yards. He also
suffered a strained left groin. But the only thing that changed for
the offense was the running back.
</P>
<P>
   ``Chris is a pro,'' Cowboys running backs coach Clarence Shelmon
said. ``He's been around. He's done it before. He gives the team a
calming effect. People know he can still make plays.''
</P>
<P>
   Warren has 10 seasons, four 1,000-yard seasons and three Pro
Bowls on his resume. Lately, however, he had little on which to
hang his helmet.
</P>
<P>
   In the past three seasons, Warren has had only two better
rushing days than the 92 yards he had Sunday. And his 25 carries
were the most since Nov. 19, 1995, when, while with Seattle, he had
29 carries for 136 yards and a touchdown against the Washington
Redskins.
</P>
<P>
   Maybe that's why his bruised right leg didn't feel so bad as he
limped out of Texas Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's tough because, yeah, I'm used to playing every down,''
Warren said. ``I want to go out there, and I know I can help the
team. But it's my role, and I chose to come here. I knew that was
what the situation would be. I just have to be ready to play
whenever I'm called.''
</P>
<P>
   Warren did lose a fumble against the Eagles, but he didn't lose
his job to Robert Chancey this time. The game was well in hand when
strong safety Tim Hauck's helmet knocked the ball out of Warren's
hand with 8:26 remaining in the fourth quarter.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was a pretty good hit,'' Warren said. ``Not much I could do
about it. I tried to get my \Rother\S hand over to cover it, but it
was too late.''
</P>
<P>
   Smith will have his injured groin re-examined Monday. Warren has
been there, done that, too. He missed the first three games of last
season with a left groin strain.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a funny injury,'' Warren said. ``You never know what the
severity is going to be. If he's down for a while, I'll be able to
play. I'll get prepared, and I'll have to come in and do my job.''
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
