<SLUG> BC-BBN-DODGERNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DODGERS MIGHT HAVE TO PAY MORE TO KEEP KARROS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRIAN DOHN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. _ Eric Karros wants to stay with the Los Angeles
Dodgers, but when Todd Zeile signed a three-year, $18 million
contract with the New York Mets late Saturday night, the cost to
keep him most likely has risen.
</P>
<P>
   Jeff Moorad, the agent for Karros, is expected to meet with the
Dodgers before spring training to discuss an extension, and no
doubt Zeile's contract will come up.
</P>
<P>
   Zeile, a third baseman by nature, will play first for the Mets
and make $6 million per year. Karros is slated to make $5 million
in 2000, but his numbers last year and over the past five years and
over his career are much better than Zeile's numbers. And at 32,
Karros is two years younger.
</P>
<P>
   Zeile batted .293 with 41 doubles, 24 homers and 98 RBI last
season with Texas. Karros hit .304 with 40 doubles, 34 homers and
112 RBI last year.
</P>
<P>
   Over the past five years, Zeile hit .269 and averaged 29
doubles, 23 homers and 87 RBI, while Karros hit .284 and averaged
29 doubles, 31 homers and 104 RBI. Karros played one more game over
the span.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think Eric has made it clear his preference is to remain in
L.A. for the rest of his career,'' Moorad said. ``At some
appropriate time in the future, I would expect to sit down with
(Dodgers managing general partner, chairman and CEO) Bob Daly and
(general manager) Kevin Malone to discuss his future. At that time
the contracts (of comparable players) I'm sure will be discussed.''
</P>
<P>
   Dreifort surgery: Dodgers right-hander Darren Dreifort had
arthroscopic surgery on his right knee Dec. 2 but is expected to be
ready for spring training.
</P>
<P>
   ``He came in for a normal check-up and said it was giving him a
little bit of a problem,'' said Dodgers general manager Kevin
Malone. ``Even if this was the season, he'd be ready in a couple of
weeks so it's nothing major, nothing that's going to impact his
season.''
</P>
<P>
   The procedure was done by Dodgers team physician Dr. Ralph
Gambardella. It was done after Dreifort came to Los Angeles for an
annual physical but complained about stiffness in the knee.
Dreifort, 27, was 13-13 with a 4.79 ERA last season.
</P>
<P>
   Extra bases: One piece of news that came out of last year's
winter meetings was Dodgers outfielder Todd Hollandsworth's demand
to be traded through Moorad, his representative. No such demand is
coming out of these meetings. ``Todd's preference is to have a
chance to play every day,'' Moorad said, but his role will be
discussed at a later date.... As expected, the Dodgers promoted
Stan Johnston to head athletic trainer and added Matt Wilson as
assistant athletic trainer.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
