<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBN-DODGERS-GREEN-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GREEN HAPPY TO BE WITH DODGERS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By LEE BARNATHAN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Shawn Green, one of the new Los Angeles Dodgers
darlings, sees his team change before his eyes, yet remains
convinced it's for the best.
</P>
<P>
   ``Playing on a winning team, that's why I came here,'' Green
said Sunday while appearing at the West Valley Community Jewish
Center. ``I know they had problems last year, but a change here and
a change there and it's a totally different team. It's not
far-fetched to go to the championship. The main pieces are there.''
</P>
<P>
   Green, making one of his first public appearances since signing
a six-year $84 million deal, clearly is happy to be here and
obviously wants the honeymoon to continue.
</P>
<P>
   He didn't speak at the ceremony to open the new Ferne Milken
Sports Complex, leaving that to Dodgers vice president Tom Lasorda.
</P>
<P>
   ``When (new Dodgers owner) Bob Daly, where we were getting ready
to sign Shawn, Bob Daly went to Shawn and said, `Shawn, do you want
to be a Dodger?''' Lasorda said. ``Shawn said, `Ever since I was 6
years old.'''
</P>
<P>
   Green later explained he rooted for the Dodgers in 1988 and the
Angels two years earlier.
</P>
<P>
   Now, of course, he has to perform if he wants the World Series
ring he seeks and didn't come close to in Toronto.
</P>
<P>
   He's aware the Dodgers want him for his left-hand bat and isn't
worried he hasn't faced National League pitchers. He reminds others
that John Olerud and Robin Ventura had successful years after
leaving the American League.
</P>
<P>
   ``The lineup looks pretty solid in the middle of the order,'' he
said.
</P>
<P>
   Other than that, he can only watch the personnel changes while
waiting for spring training to begin.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm looking forward to meeting my new teammates,'' he said,
``whoever they are.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-13-99 0215EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
