School, said that the gun industry found itself on the defensive
because gun control advocates successfully changed the terms of the
debate from the right to bear arms to public health. And, just as
with tobacco, once the debate was reframed to emphasize the cost to
society, the roadblocks to industry regulation began to fall.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is not going to solve all gun crimes,'' Lytton said.
``But if it is true that a significant number of guns are being
sold irresponsibly then changing the practices of manufacturers can
change that.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
