<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Macintosh operating system dissected
 &HT;    By Charles Haddad
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ See and read about OS 9, the latest version of the Mac
operating system, in the December issue of MacAddict. The magazine
features a cover story in which nearly every aspect of the system
is depicted graphically. It also offers tips on how to get the best
out of OS 9.
</P>
<P>
   ON CD-ROM
</P>
<P>
   Sid Meier has released a sequel to his popular live-action Civil
War game ``Gettysburg.'' The newest game, using the same format and
technology, is called ``Antietam.'' It's based on the famous Civil
War battle of the same name. The game is available only for PCs
with Windows 95 or higher.
</P>
<P>
   Legos have gone digital. The famous Danish toy company has
released a computer game based on its plastic building blocks.
Called ``Lego Rock Raiders,'' the game lets players command a
geological survey ship on an uncharted planet. The game is
available only for PCs with Windows 95 or higher. A Sony
PlayStation version of the game is scheduled to be released early
next year.
</P>
<P>
   ONLINE
</P>
<P>
   Have you ever wondered about the complete history of Christmas?
Well, now you can find out this and much more about the holiday at
a Web site called How Christmas Works. It's part of a larger
service on the Web called How Things Work.
</P>
<P>
   On the Christmas page, you can find out whether Dec. 25 was
really the day Jesus was born, how the tradition of gift-giving
began, and when and why people started keeping small evergreen
trees to celebrate the holiday. You'll find this site at www
</P>
<P>
   .howstuffworks.com
</P>
<P>
   /christmas.htm.
</P>
