<SLUG> BC-NFK-NEWSFLASH14-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Dad wants son returned to Cuba
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ A 6-year-old boy is the focus of a United States-Cuba
tug of war over who should have custody of him. Elian Gonzalez
crossed the ocean between Cuba and Florida in a boat with his
mother, stepfather and others. They were trying to reach the United
States. Many Cubans feel they would have a better life in America.
However, his mother, stepfather and nine others died when their
boat sank. The boy was found floating in an inner tube off the
coast of Florida.
</P>
<P>
   Now his father, who lives in Cuba, wants Elian returned to the
island nation, which is about 90 miles south of Key West, Fla. His
great-aunt and great-uncle want to raise him in Miami.
</P>
<P>
   JURY FINDS MLK JR. KILLED BY CONSPIRACY
</P>
<P>
   A Memphis, Tenn., jury decided last week that more than one
person conspired, or worked together, to kill the Rev. Martin
Luther King Jr.
</P>
<P>
   The civil rights leader was shot in 1968 standing outside a
Memphis hotel. About a year later, the accused white assassin,
James Earl Ray, pleaded guilty to the murder and was sentenced to
99 years in prison. Ray later said he didn't do it and tried for 30
years to prove his innocence. He died last year.
</P>
<P>
   The King family felt that Ray was innocent. The family sued Loyd
Jowers because, six years ago, he claimed he paid someone other
than Ray to kill King. The Kings' lawyer said Jowers was part of a
big conspiracy involving the Mafia and agents of the federal
government. He said King was targeted because of his opposition to
the Vietnam War and plans for a huge ``poor people's march'' on
Washington.
</P>
<P>
   The jury agreed there was a conspiracy.
</P>
<P>
   DISNEY PULLS VILLAIN
</P>
<P>
   The Walt Disney Co. has agreed to change a sombrero-wearing
character in the ``Toy Story 2'' video game because it offended
some Hispanics.
</P>
<P>
   One level of the game features a villain with a mustache and a
sombrero (a large hat), which Hispanic activists said was a Mexican
stereotype.
</P>
<P>
   ``We feel it's degrading, it's dehumanizing. It stereotypes
Mexicans as villains,'' said Oscar de la Torre, a counselor at
Santa Monica High School in California.
</P>
<P>
   The character does not appear in the ``Toy Story 2'' movie.
</P>
<P>
   ``We regret that a portion of the game was offensive,'' a Disney
spokeswoman said.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
