   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MORSE-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ San Franciscans are facing two
less than perfect choices for mayor in the runoff here Tuesday,
even though incumbent Willie Brown and challenger Tom Ammiano come
on strong as symbols. The first question voters should ask
themselves before Tuesday's election is who do they want as mayor
if there's an earthquake? By ROB MORSE.
</P>
<P>
   ROBISON-COLUMN (Austin, Texas) _ In the game of lowered
expectations that we call presidential ``debates,'' Gov. George W.
Bush survived his first two challenges, and his supporters breathed
huge sighs of relief. His performances would have earned him a
``C-minus'' or worse from many high school speech teachers, but his
White House campaign is still alive and well because he didn't say
or do anything stupid. By CLAY ROBISON.
