</HEADLINE>
 OUTPUT TEST8 TO NYT TO NYT  &HT;    (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients 
 &HT;    By A REPORTER 
 &HT;    c.1999 A Newspaper 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here's the body of our story. We'll use several typographical
characters to test.
</P>
<P>
   Here's an (at) sign:  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Here's an exclamation point: !
</P>
<P>
   Here's a dollar sign: $
</P>
<P>
   Here's a percent sign: %
</P>
<P>
   Here's an ampersand: &AMP;
</P>
<P>
   Here's a left parenthesis: (
</P>
<P>
   Here's a right parenthesis: )
</P>
<P>
   Here's a plus: +
</P>
<P>
   Here's a comma: ,
</P>
<P>
   Here's a hypen: -
</P>
<P>
   Here's a period: .
</P>
<P>
   Here's a slash: /
</P>
<P>
   Here's a colon: :
</P>
<P>
   Here's a semicolon: ;
</P>
<P>
   Here's a question mark: ?
</P>
<P>
   Here's an em dash: -
