<HEADLINE>
`BUENA VISTA' MOVING; `RED VIOLIN' PROVOCATIVE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by NewkTimes News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Buena Vista Social Club'' (DVD) _ One of this
year's best films arrives just in time for Christmas. The reunion
of Cuban jazz musicians, instigated by Ry Cooder, makes for a
moving story and sumptuous soundtrack. On DVD, the sound is even
better than it was in the theater.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Red Violin'' (DVD) _ Moviemakers always seem to be
fascinated by following an object through history. They've done it
with everything from a gun to a yellow Rolls-Royce. In this
provocative story, it's a violin that changes hands over and over
again. And it's done to great effect in this one.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   BOND IS BIG: The James Bond titles continue to be big sellers
for MGM, which sold this fall nearly 1.3 million copies on DVD and
1.5 milion on VHS of seven repackaged films that included war
horses such as ``Goldfinger'' (1964) and ``Thunderball'' (1965).
The studio will put on another big push when ``The World Is Not
Enough'' is released to home viewers in the late spring.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NEW ON DVD: ``Shakespeare in Love,'' the Best Picture Oscar
winner, is out on DVD and it's terrific. Aside from a crisp
picture, there is a deleted ending that's included. (Thank goodness
they didn't use it). Also, there's revealing commentary from the
cast and crew and biographical material on Shakespeare that
enhances an appreciation for both the Bard and the movie.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: Dec. 21: ``Run Lola Run'' (DVD), ``American
Pie'' (DVD), ``Tampopo'' (DVD), ``Summer of Sam,'' `thics for the
New Millennium,'' ``The Adventures of Elmo in Grouchland,'' ``A
Taxing Woman'' (DVD), ``The Funeral'' (DVD), ``K-911'' (DVD),
``Supercop 2,'' ``Witness to the Mob.'' Dec. 28: ``Dudley
Do-Right,'' ``Better Than Chocolate,'' ``Desert Blue'' (DVD). Jan.
4: ``The Thomas Crown Affair'' (DVD), ``Sayonara,'' Jan. 11: ``The
Art of Buster Keaton'' (DVD), ``The Extreme Adventures of Super
Dave.'' Jan. 18: ``An Ideal Husband,'' ``The Hitchhiker,'' ``From
Dusk to Dawn 3,'' ``The 13th Warrior.'' ``The Wood'' (DVD). Jan.
25: ``Runaway Bride,'' ``My Life So Far,'' ``The Sex Monster,''
``My Son the Fanatic,'' ``The Tempest,'' ``Woman Wanted.'' Feb. 1:
``The Cabinet of Dr. Caligari,'' ``Nosferatu.''
</P>
