   SCI-STONEAGE-FASHIONS (Undated) _ According to three
anthropologists, it is time to toss aside the hidebound cliches of
Paleolithic woman. Researchers have found evidence that the women
of the so-called upper Paleolithic era were far more accomplished,
economically powerful and sartorially gifted than previously
believed. By Natalie Angier.
</P>
