<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ The year 2000 will mark the 25th season of
``Austin City Limits,'' the PBS show that has featured everyone
from Tom Waits to Garth Brooks to George Jones to Sheryl Crow.
Brooks, in fact, has compared playing ``ACL'' to playing in the
World Series. We look at a show that predated MTV and VH1 and (with
its emphasis where it should be, on the music) is still going
strong. By DAVE FERMAN. Story will move in ``e'' entertainment
