<P>
   MIDEAST-ISRAEL (Jerusalem) _ After hours of impassioned debate _
and just two days before talks begin in Washington _ Israel's
parliament narrowly endorsed Prime Minister Ehud Barak's quest for
a comprehensive peace settlement with Syria. Israel will pay ``a
heavy territorial price,'' Barak acknowledged in an emotional plea
for parliamentary support Monday. But failure to pursue peace with
Damascus ``could cost us in blood,'' he said. By William A. Orme
Jr.
</P>
