   GM-NAZI-COMPENSATION (Frankfurt) _ General Motors Corp.'s German
subsidiary said Monday that it would contribute to a fund to
compensate forced laborers during the Nazi era, the first American
company to accept responsibility for abuses under Hitler's regime.
The decision came as attorneys representing former workers appeared
close to a final deal with the German government and industry to
create a compensation fund of about $5.3 billion. By Edmund L.
Andrews.
</P>
<P>
   INDIA-NEW-CAPITALISM (Bangalore, India) _ The slight,
bespectacled computer engineer who starts each day by cleaning the
toilet in his family's apartment hardly seems to be the new
archetype of a wildly successful Indian entrepreneur, boldly
steering his country away from decades of socialism and into a new
era of capitalist growth. But in India, where a long line of Hindu
ascetics have captured the popular imagination, it is fitting that
one of the country's most influential champions of capitalism and
hottest software tycoons should be a man who lives as if he were a
humble clerk. By Celia Dugger.
</P>
