<DATE_TIME> 1999-12-13 17:20 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7680 &Cx1f; tie-z
u a BC-CIR-PHONE-DESIGNER-AR     12-13 0155
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CIR-PHONE-DESIGNER-ART-2NDTAKE-NYT </SLUG>
 
Undated: Just like new.''  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The new 8200 series, introduced at the Kenzo show, takes the
fashion statement still further. The three-ounce 8210 phone has six
easily interchangeable faceplates.
</P>
<P>
   But that's already yesterday's news. Like any good designer,
Nuovo said, he lives five years out. To demonstrate, he reached
into his briefcase and pulled out a pair of prototypes. Impossibly
thin and predictably futuristic, these two concept phones have
everything: built-in cameras, fully readable Web pages, personal
organizers and a large dose of snazz.
</P>
<P>
   By the time those phones, or phones like them, are on the
market, Nuovo may well have left the world of communications
fashion. ``My dream is to someday have a jazz club in Monterey and
play _ that's something I passionately want to do,'' he said,
striking a restless note. ``The ultimate dream is to stay
creative.''
</P>
</TEXT>
