 For Release TUESDAY AMs, December 14, 1999  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following stories for use by
NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call  &UR; 888-346-9867  &LR; or  &UR; 888-603-1036 &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-KNESSET (Jerusalem) _ Prime Minister Ehud Barak goes to
the Knesset to get a vote of support for his diplomatic initiative
with Syria. Instead of establishing a consensus, however, the
parliamentary procedure descends into chaos. By Charles M. Sennott.
750 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MILITARY-GAYS (Washington) _ US Rep. Barney Frank says Al Gore
should go beyond criticizing administration policy on gays in the
military and support the policy's termination. By Ann Scales. 900
words. (w and a coding)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POLITICS (p) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-DEBATE (Des Moines) _ Appealing to a cable TV audience,
George W. Bush's five GOP rivals seek a pre-holiday boost in
attention _ hopefully at his expense. By Curtis Wilkie. 1200 words.
(Late)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   GENES-PATENT (Undated) _ A rare disease highlights an issue of
the brave new world of genetics: The test to identify carriers of a
devastating disease is patented by the hospital that created it.
The hospital charges a royalty for its use and limits who can use
it. By Richard Saltus. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   MA-MENTAL (Boston) _ Massachusetts officials, psychologists and
relatives of mental patients say it's time mental illness is
covered by insurance the same as physical illness. By Dolores.
Kong. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS (e) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TV-SPLITUP (Boston) _ Boston's premier anchor partners, Natalie
Jacobsen and Chet Curtis, announce they're ending their 24-year
marriage, but will continue in their TV jobs. By Don Aucoin. 900
words.
</P>
<P>
   APPRECIATE-HELLER (Undated) _ An appreciation of ``Catch 22''
author Joseph Heller, dead of a heart attack. By Mark Feeney.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MASSMUTUAL-TRAVELERS (Undated) _ MassMutual says it is
considering buying the long-term-care business of Travelers Group,
the giant insurance company that is part of Citigroup. By Lynnley
Browning. 500 words.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-FUNDING (Undated) _ Andersen Consulting, which has
helped fund more than two dozen Internet companies, announces an
ambitous program to invest $1 billion over the next five years
mostly in business-to-business e-commerce startups. By Ronald
Rosenberg. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   HARVARDNET-FUNDING (Undated) _ Microsoft cofounder Paul Allen
and others pump $70 million more into fast Net DSL access provider
HarvardNet to help it expand throughout the Northeast. By Peter
Howe. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   COMPAQ-DMGI (Undated) _ Compaq and Internet venture-fund company
CMGI Inc. plan to form a joint venture with the Shanghai
government's investment arm to offer Internet services in China. By
Hiawatha Bray. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
</P>
