<SLUG> BC-APPRECIATE-HELLER-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
JOSEPH HELLER, 76; FAMED FOR WAR NOVEL `CATCH-22' 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Includes excerpt; e and a coding)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MARK FEENEY  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Joseph Heller, whose black-comic novel of World War II,
``Catch-22,'' contributed an enduring phrase to the English
language, died Sunday at his East Hampton, N.Y., home of a heart
attack. He was 76.
</P>
