<P>
   POSTAL-CRUSH (Los Angeles) -- With Christmas 11 days away and on
the heels of a big buying weekend, Monday traditionally is the
busiest mailing day of the year. And it was, based on lines at many
area post offices that extended outside as harried shoppers raced
to get gifts in the mail. UPS, Mailboxes etc., and other private
delivery companies reported heavy traffic, and post offices were
clogged with crowds on Sunday, the first of two Sundays with
special hours for Christmas gift givers. By Jesse Hiestand. (Will
