Welfare Commission, which has the authority to raise the minimum
wage with or without approval from the state Legislature, will hold
a public hearing Wednesday in downtown Los Angeles. The hearing is
the first step in what is expected to be a year-long process to
decide whether to increase the state's minumim wage from it's
current $5.75 an hour. Every two years, the commission is required
to review the current minimum wage. By Chris Sieroty. (Will move on
the ``f'' financial news wire.)
