603-1036 or (888) 346-9867.)
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Center right)
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-ECON (Tokyo) _ The Japanese finance minister said Monday
that he expected the government to begin trying to wean the
country's shaky economy away from its reliance on public borrowing,
a practice that has made Japan one of the biggest debtor nations.
By Stephanie Strom.
</P>
<P>
