<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KCI-GROWTH-2ndTAKE-KAN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
KCI POISED FOR GROWTH IN PASSENGERS, AIRLINES 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By RANDOLPH HEASTER  
 c. 1999 Kansas City Star   KANSAS CITY, Mo. _ KCI's only direct
international flights are to Toronto on Air Canada.
<TEXT>
<P>
   All About Travel's Sudeikis agreed that KCI's strategy so far
has worked.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think they've struck the delicate balance between attracting
low-fare carriers and keeping the revenues high enough for the
major airlines,'' she said. ``But we don't want to scare away the
big guys.''
</P>
<P>
   Sudeikis said Kansas City still lacks some needed service, such
as nonstops to San Francisco and Miami. In addition, only Southwest
offers nonstop service to Las Vegas, one of the most popular
destinations from Kansas City.
</P>
<P>
   ``There are a couple of holes, but I think they've done a good
job overall,'' she said. ``We're doing pretty well considering
every major carrier is still here, which can't be said for lot of
cities our size.''
</P>
<P>
   Through September, KCI's total passenger traffic was up 6
percent over the same period last year, to 8.61 million.
</P>
<P>
   In 1998, the airport ranked 37th among North America's busiest
airports with 10.95 million passengers, according to the Airports
Council International. In 1992, KCI ranked 40th.
</P>
<P>
   Another indicator of KCI's growth can be seen in its comparison
with Indianapolis, which also is without a significant hub.
</P>
<P>
   In 1992, KCI had 1 million more passengers than Indianapolis
International Airport. In 1998, that gap grew to 3.6 million
passengers.
</P>
<P>
   Teresa Loar, chairwoman of the Kansas City Council's aviation
committee, attributes the growth to low fares and the airport's
convenience.
</P>
<P>
   ``When you can unload your baggage and walk to your car within
100 yards, that's pretty convenient,'' she said. ``Also, we're
drawing people from all over the region because it's cheaper to fly
from here. If I had a dollar for every Wichita resident I've sat
next to on my flights...''
</P>
<P>
   Loar also credited aviation department officials with marketing
KCI effectively in recent years.
</P>
<P>
   With congestion being a problem at so many metropolitan
airports, Loar and others believe KCI can continue to add service.
</P>
<P>
   ``All the signs are good, but we as a business community need to
support the nonstops when we get them,'' Sudeikis said. ``Travel in
general has grown so dramatically. When an airline goes out and
offers us a key nonstop flight, we have to deliver when that
happens.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
